    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>We have a HOBO MX TidbiT 400 autonomous temperature sensor and want to see how it compares to a "real" Temperature sensor.</p>

<p>I think it is as simple as setting up the HOBO to record for a couple days, and let it hang in the test tank at the same height as the T sensor from a SBE CTD.</p>

<p>Probably want the driver to be running on the SBE CTD, so we can just get the data from Oceans 3.0</p>

<p>This is strictly and engineering test, no Data Stewardship or DAQ requirements on this one.</p>

<p> </p>
            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <br/>

