            <p>Removed Nov 07, ~15:37 UTC</p>
        </td></tr>
                <tr id="comment-header-667727"><td bgcolor="#f0f0f0">
            Comment by  
                                                        <a class="user-hover" rel="shanetheobald" id="word_commented_shanetheobald" href="https://jira.oceannetworks.ca/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=shanetheobald">Shane Theobald</a>
                                        <font size="-2">
            [
                <font color="#336699">15 Nov 2024</font>

                            ]
            </font>

        </td></tr>
        <tr id="comment-body-667727"><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
            <p>One thing I did notice in the data is the HOBO temperature, compared to the reference temperature, was lower and had an accuracy of ~ 0.015 - 0.02 when cooling but was ~ 0.35 - 0.4 when temperature was rising. </p>

<p>Definitely not scientific, just an observation.</p>
        </td></tr>
